$interpreted: Child: Waaaahh!! Don't eat me!
Nolva: Granny! Watch out!
Nolva: Are you okay, Granny?
Granny: Oh dear... This old biddy was nearly done for... thank heavens you were here. Are you with the Guards?
Nolva: Yup~ Don't worry, Granny, we're all here to keep everyone safe~
Kittyeyes: Nolva!!
Kittyeyes: What did I tell you! Stop charging about on your own, or you'll get yourself into trouble!!
Nolva: Oh, right! ...I'm sorry. I saw Granny here take a spill and hurried over...
Roger: Well now, look who's talking. Save it for later, we've got a situation on our hands!
Guard: Roger!! We can't hold out here much longer!
Roger: I'll be right there—
Guard: It's useless! There're too many monsters, Hansen and the others are already...
Nolva: Hansen... No, it can't be...
Guard: Retreat! If we don't pull out now we'll all be dead as dogmeat!
Kittyeyes: Wait! If we retreat, who'll save the villagers of Kullu?
Guard: Send the army in instead! We'll be no good to them if we can't even save ourselves!
Kittyeyes: There's no time for that!
Kittyeyes: It was because the troops were understaffed in the first place that everybody banded together in the Civilian Guard to help each other out!
Roger: Jeff! What's the situ—
Jeff: What are you still doing here!? The monsters are coming!
Roger: ...Dammit!
Roger: Halt!
Kittyeyes: Roger!
Roger: Don't answer back. Everybody retreat! I'll cover our tail.
Roger: Go go go!
Sneaky Guard: Is this... the right thing to do?
Stealthy Guard: Stop your nagging and just get on with it!
Sneaky Guard: ...Pshh, fine!
Villager: Hey, stop! Where d'you think you're going with everybody's food!?
Stealthy Guard: Anyplace we'll still be alive to enjoy it! Only a fool would hang about and meet death with you lot here!!
Villager: You can't...
Villager: Thieves! Everybody, come quick!
Sneaky Guard: R-Roger...
Roger: I came as soon as I heard. Are you the stinkin' thieves?
Kittyeyes: Huh? How could you! Aren't we all in this together!?
Stealthy Guard: Yeah, right!
Stealthy Guard: We all heard how you fled from Kullu. The village is totally unguarded!
Villager: What... Is that true!? Roger?
Granny: Good gravy... This old biddy's being left for monster chow...
Kittyeyes: W-wait a minute! Now listen up, everybody! I know we can beat those monsters, as long as we all stick together!
Roger: ...Run, if you're gonna run.
Kittyeyes: Roger!
Roger: But leave the food. It doesn't belong to you!
Stealthy Guard: Hmph, stop me if you can!!
Nolva: Gah. I'll gather it back up...
Roger: Come here, Kittyeyes.
Roger: It was true, what those two said. When the monsters arrived at Kullu, we weren't able to stop 'em.
Roger: I'll stay here. You and Nolva can slip away quietly.
Kittyeyes: No way! Everyone's fought so hard to get this far! I know we can make it if we try—
Roger: This isn't like last time. There's far too many of them! Do you seriously think the Civilian Guard stand a chance here without the troops!?
Kittyeyes: But... I-I-I'll run to Totemtaff and plead for the Bears' help! There's no way Dagger will just sit back if we're in danger!
Roger: It's monsters, monsters, monsters, all the way from here to Totemtaff! You'd never make it alone!
Kittyeyes: I don't know! Stop yelling at me! But whatever happens, I'm not leaving you!
Roger: Of all times, you're gonna pick now to throw a tantrum!? Do what I tell you, Kittyeyes!
Nolva: (Has even Roger given up hope...?)
Nolva: (...But there are still so many of us...)
Nolva: ......
Nolva: ...Waverlyde...?
Nolva: ......
Nolva: ...Yes, Waverlyde...
Nolva: ...You're right. It's too early to be giving up.
Nolva: After all, I've still got you, my secret weapon~
Nolva: Let's go, Waverlyde—on to Totemtaff, to ask for their help.
